{
  "name": "Approval Step 1: Parse TES-070 Document",
  "version": "3.1.0",
  "description": "Parse a TES-070 approval document and generate framework-compatible test scenarios for ENHANCEMENTS (E in RICE)",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Execute Step 1: Parse TES-070 and Generate Test Scenarios\n\n**IMPORTANT:** Load steering file '10_JSON_Generation_Best_Practices.md' using discloseContext tool for BLOCKING requirements on COMPLETE JSON generation.\n\nYou are parsing a TES-070 approval document to create framework-compatible test scenarios for REGRESSION TESTING. This is for APPROVAL WORKFLOWS (Enhancements/Extensions - E in RICE), NOT Interfaces. Extension IDs start with EXT_ (e.g., EXT_FIN_004).\n\n**STEP 1-2: USER SELECTION (Interactive)**\n1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects client\n2. List TES-070 approval documents in Projects/{ClientName}/TES-070/Approval_TES070s_For_Regression_Testing/ → User selects document\n   - Look for *.docx files in this folder\n   - These are ORIGINAL TES-070 documents for regression testing\n   - Example: SoNH_TES-070 - EXT_FIN_004 Expense Invoice Approval Test Results Document.docx\n   - Extension IDs start with EXT_ (not INT_)\n\n**STEP 3: ANALYZE DOCUMENT**\n3. Run: python ReusableTools/tes070_analyzer.py \"{document_path}\"\n4. The analyzer creates a JSON file with the same name + \"_analysis.json\"\n5. Read the COMPLETE analysis JSON file to extract:\n   - Extension ID (e.g., EXT_FIN_004) - from document title or test summary\n   - Transaction type (ExpenseInvoice, ManualJournal, CashLedgerTransaction)\n   - FSM module (Payables, General Ledger, Cash Management)\n   - Actual scenario count from test_summary.actual_scenario_count\n   - All test scenarios with details\n\n**STEP 4: UNDERSTAND TES-070 STRUCTURE (CRITICAL)**\nThe TES-070 analyzer output has TWO types of scenario entries:\n- **TOC Entries** (first N scenarios): Only have title, no test_steps, no images, no description\n- **Detailed Scenarios** (last N scenarios): Have test_steps, images, descriptions, results\n\nYou MUST use the DETAILED scenarios (the ones with test_steps and images), NOT the TOC entries.\n\n**How to identify detailed scenarios:**\n- Check if scenario has test_steps array with length > 0\n- Check if scenario has images array with length > 0\n- Check if scenario has description field with actual content\n- These are typically in the second half of the scenarios array\n\n**STEP 5: EXTRACT SCENARIO DETAILS**\n6. For EACH detailed scenario in the TES-070, extract:\n   - scenario_id (e.g., \"3.1\", \"3.2\") - from title field\n   - title - clean version without scenario_id prefix\n   - description - from description field in JSON\n   - vendor_class (GHR, EMP, OTHER) - infer from title/description\n   - authority_code (AP1, PR1, etc.) - extract from description or test_steps\n   - amount - extract from test_steps or use reasonable default\n   - expected_route (AUTO, BOA, Agency, PayrollMgr) - infer from title\n   - expected_final_status (Released, Rejected, Returned) - infer from title\n\n**PARSING RULES:**\n- Extract scenario_id: Look for pattern \"X.Y\" at start of title\n- Clean title: Remove scenario_id and \"Scenario:\" prefix\n- Infer vendor_class from keywords:\n  * \"garnishment\" or \"GHR\" → GHR\n  * \"employee\" or \"EMP\" → EMP  \n  * \"other\" or \"OTHER\" → OTHER\n- Infer authority_code from keywords:\n  * \"authority code = AP1\" or \"AP1\" → AP1\n  * \"authority code = PR1\" or \"PR1\" → PR1\n  * If not mentioned → null (will be omitted from invoice_data)\n- Infer amount from keywords:\n  * \"less than $1,000\" or \"< $1,000\" → \"500.00\"\n  * \"at least $1,000\" or \">= $1,000\" → \"1500.00\"\n  * If not mentioned → \"100.00\" (default)\n- Infer expected_route from keywords:\n  * \"auto approved\" → AUTO\n  * \"routed to BOA\" → BOA\n  * \"routed to Agency\" → Agency\n  * \"routed to Payroll\" → PayrollMgr\n- Infer expected_final_status from keywords:\n  * \"approved\" → Released\n  * \"rejected\" → Rejected\n  * \"returned\" → Returned\n\n**STEP 6: GENERATE COMPLETE FRAMEWORK JSON**\n7. Generate framework-compatible JSON with ALL scenarios at:\n   Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{extension_id}_auto_approval_test.json\n\n**CRITICAL: You MUST generate ALL scenarios in ONE complete JSON file. NO partial generation. NO \"add the rest manually\". This is a BLOCKING requirement from 10_JSON_Generation_Best_Practices.md.**\n\n**JSON STRUCTURE:**\n```json\n{\n  \"extension_id\": \"EXT_FIN_004\",\n  \"interface_type\": \"approval\",\n  \"description\": \"Expense Invoice Approval - Regression Test\",\n  \"scenarios\": [\n    {\n      \"scenario_id\": \"3.1\",\n      \"title\": \"GHR Vendor Auto Approval\",\n      \"description\": \"Garnishment invoice auto approved for GHR vendor\",\n      \"steps\": [\n        {\n          \"number\": 1,\n          \"description\": \"Login to FSM\",\n          \"action\": {\n            \"type\": \"fsm_login\",\n            \"url\": \"{{FSM_PORTAL_URL}}\",\n            \"username\": \"{{FSM_USERNAME}}\",\n            \"password\": \"{{state.password}}\",\n            \"auth_method\": \"Cloud Identities\"\n          },\n          \"expected_result\": \"Successfully logged into FSM\",\n          \"result\": \"PENDING\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"number\": 2,\n          \"description\": \"Navigate to Payables\",\n          \"action\": {\n            \"type\": \"fsm_payables\",\n            \"operation\": \"navigate_to_payables\"\n          },\n          \"expected_result\": \"Payables application loaded\",\n          \"result\": \"PENDING\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"number\": 3,\n          \"description\": \"Create expense invoice for GHR vendor\",\n          \"action\": {\n            \"type\": \"fsm_payables\",\n            \"operation\": \"create_invoice\",\n            \"invoice_data\": {\n              \"company\": \"10\",\n              \"vendor\": \"GHR\",\n              \"invoice_number\": \"AUTO-{{state.run_group}}\",\n              \"invoice_date\": \"{{TODAY_YYYYMMDD}}\",\n              \"due_date\": \"{{TODAY_PLUS_7_YYYYMMDD}}\",\n              \"invoice_amount\": \"100.00\",\n              \"description\": \"GHR Vendor Auto Approval - Automated test\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"expected_result\": \"Invoice created successfully\",\n          \"result\": \"PENDING\",\n          \"screenshot\": \"01_invoice_created\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"number\": 4,\n          \"description\": \"Submit invoice for approval\",\n          \"action\": {\n            \"type\": \"fsm_payables\",\n            \"operation\": \"submit_for_approval\"\n          },\n          \"expected_result\": \"Invoice submitted for approval workflow\",\n          \"result\": \"PENDING\",\n          \"screenshot\": \"02_approval_submitted\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"number\": 5,\n          \"description\": \"Navigate to Work Units\",\n          \"action\": {\n            \"type\": \"fsm_workunits\",\n            \"operation\": \"navigate\"\n          },\n          \"expected_result\": \"Work Units page loaded\",\n          \"result\": \"PENDING\",\n          \"screenshot\": \"03_work_units_page\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"number\": 6,\n          \"description\": \"Wait for approval workflow completion\",\n          \"action\": {\n            \"type\": \"fsm_workunits\",\n            \"operation\": \"wait_for_completion\",\n            \"process_name\": \"Expense Invoice Approval\",\n            \"timeout\": 300\n          },\n          \"expected_result\": \"Approval workflow completed\",\n          \"result\": \"PENDING\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"number\": 7,\n          \"description\": \"Verify workflow completed successfully\",\n          \"action\": {\n            \"type\": \"fsm_workunits\",\n            \"operation\": \"verify_status\",\n            \"expected_status\": \"Completed\"\n          },\n          \"expected_result\": \"Work unit status is Completed\",\n          \"result\": \"PENDING\",\n          \"screenshot\": \"04_workflow_completed\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**STEP 7: GENERATE STANDARD STEPS FOR EACH SCENARIO**\n8. For EACH scenario, generate these standard 7 steps:\n   - Step 1: Login to FSM\n   - Step 2: Navigate to module (Payables/GL/Cash)\n   - Step 3: Create transaction with scenario-specific data\n   - Step 4: Submit for approval\n   - Step 5: Navigate to Work Units\n   - Step 6: Wait for workflow completion\n   - Step 7: Verify final status\n\n9. Customize Step 3 (Create transaction) based on transaction type:\n\n   **For ExpenseInvoice (Payables):**\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"type\": \"fsm_payables\",\n     \"operation\": \"create_invoice\",\n     \"invoice_data\": {\n       \"company\": \"10\",\n       \"vendor\": \"{vendor_class}\",\n       \"invoice_number\": \"AUTO-{{state.run_group}}\",\n       \"invoice_date\": \"{{TODAY_YYYYMMDD}}\",\n       \"due_date\": \"{{TODAY_PLUS_7_YYYYMMDD}}\",\n       \"invoice_amount\": \"{amount}\",\n       \"authority_code\": \"{authority_code}\",\n       \"description\": \"{clean_title} - Automated test\"\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n   Note: If authority_code is null, omit the \"authority_code\" field entirely from invoice_data.\n\n   **For ManualJournal (GL):**\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"type\": \"fsm_gl\",\n     \"operation\": \"create_journal\",\n     \"journal_data\": {\n       \"company\": \"10\",\n       \"journal_id\": \"AUTO-{{state.run_group}}\",\n       \"description\": \"{clean_title} - Automated test\",\n       \"amount\": \"{amount}\"\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n   **For CashLedgerTransaction (Cash):**\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"type\": \"fsm_cash\",\n     \"operation\": \"create_transaction\",\n     \"transaction_data\": {\n       \"company\": \"10\",\n       \"transaction_id\": \"AUTO-{{state.run_group}}\",\n       \"description\": \"{clean_title} - Automated test\",\n       \"amount\": \"{amount}\"\n     }\n   }\n   ```\n\n**STEP 8: VALIDATE GENERATED JSON**\n10. After generating the JSON file, validate it:\n    ```\n    python ReusableTools/validate_json.py Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{extension_id}_auto_approval_test.json\n    ```\n11. If validation fails, fix the JSON and validate again\n12. Do NOT proceed until validation passes\n\n**STEP 9: SHOW SUMMARY**\n13. Display to user:\n   - Extension ID: {extension_id}\n   - Transaction Type: {transaction_type}\n   - Total Scenarios Generated: {count}\n   - Output File: Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{extension_id}_auto_approval_test.json\n   - Validation: PASSED\n   - List all scenario IDs and titles\n\n14. Confirm file created and validated successfully\n\n**STEP 10: NEXT STEPS**\n15. Tell user:\n    - ✅ Step 1 complete!\n    - 📄 {count} test scenarios generated and validated\n    - 🚀 Next: Click \"Approval Step 2: Execute Approval Tests\"\n    - Framework will execute all scenarios automatically\n\n**IMPORTANT NOTES:**\n- Generated JSON is framework-compatible\n- Uses {{state.variable}} for runtime interpolation\n- Uses {{TODAY_YYYYMMDD}} for current date\n- Uses {{state.run_group}} for unique identifiers\n- All scenarios follow standard 7-step pattern\n- Credentials loaded from .env files at runtime\n- Framework handles all execution automatically\n- This is for ENHANCEMENTS (EXT_), not INTERFACES (INT_)\n\n**TROUBLESHOOTING:**\n- If TES-070 parsing fails: Check document format, verify file path\n- If no detailed scenarios found: Check if scenarios array has entries with test_steps\n- If scenario details unclear: Use reasonable defaults based on parsing rules\n- If transaction type unknown: Ask user to specify\n- If validation fails: Review error messages, fix JSON structure, validate again\n- If vendor/amount unclear: Use defaults (vendor=GHR, amount=100.00)\n\nAfter completion, tell the user: 'Step 1 complete. Generated and validated {count} test scenarios at: Projects/{ClientName}/TestScripts/approval/{extension_id}_auto_approval_test.json. Run Approval Step 2 to execute automated testing.'"
  },
  "enabled": true,
  "workspaceFolderName": "Automated_Testing",
  "shortName": "approval-step1-parse-tes070"
}